From 0000000000000000000000000000000000000000 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: cj-vana <cj@depth23.online>
Date: Sat, 16 May 2026 12:38:13 -0600
Subject: [PATCH 5/9] Add hop-aware bot coordination, utility commands, and
 bounded delays

Adds new utility commands (TIME, LORA, ID, NEIGHBORS), neighbor tracking,
per-hop response delay coordination, received_at_timestamp tracking, and
personalized ack targets.

Tunes the response coordinator so multi-hop senders actually get responses:

- Hop step default: 5000ms -> 1500ms per hop
- Adds BOT_HOP_BIAS_MAX_MILLIS cap of 8000ms on total hop delay
- Pending TTL: 15000ms -> 45000ms
- Bumps BOT_PREFS_VERSION 2 -> 3 to force defaults on existing bots that
  already saved the broken 5000ms hop_step_ms value

With the old defaults a 3-hop channel sender would queue a response at
~16400ms (1200 base + 200 channel + 15000 hop bias) which exceeded the
15000ms TTL, so poll() always returned READY_EXPIRED and the bot stayed
silent for multi-hop senders. New worst case (10+ hops, full jitter,
queue depth 10) is ~13600ms, well under the new 45000ms TTL.
